Package org.ginsim.gui.graph

Interface GraphGUIHelper<G extends Graph<V,​E>,​V,​E extends Edge<V>>

  • Type Parameters:
    G - the graph
    V - the vertex
    E - the edge
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DynamicGraphGUIHelper, HierarchicalTransitionGraphGUIHelper, ReducedGraphGUIHelper, RegulatoryGraphGUIHelper, TrapSpaceTreeGUIHelper, TreeGUIHelper
    public interface GraphGUIHelper<G extends Graph<V,​E>,​V,​E extends Edge<V>>
    GUI-side helper for a graph type. A helper is a singleton dedicated to a specific graph type. It provides GUI components required to visualize and edit a graph. Implementors must be called with the same pattern: 'GraphClassName' in order to have the GraphGUIHelperFactory able to create their instances through introspective access Implementations must be annotated "@MetaInfServices( GraphGUIHelper.class)" to be discovered at runtime
    Author:
    Aurelien Naldi
